= Authoring Stories in JSON =

== Story Shape ==
Top-level fields:
* ''id'' (unique story key)
* ''name''
* ''description''
* ''start_node''
* ''nodes'' (map of node id -> node object)

== Node Types ==
Common types:
* ''dialogue''
* ''journal''
* ''discovery''
* ''ending''

Each node can include:
* ''text'' (list of lines)
* ''speaker''
* ''choices''
* ''triggers''
* ''on_start'' actions
* ''requires'' conditions

== Choices ==
Each choice can include:
* ''text''
* ''next'' (target node)
* ''requires''
* ''actions''

Weighted branching is supported with ''weighted_outcomes''.

== Variables and Flags ==
Use actions to set and mutate state:
* ''set_var'' for int/bool/string variables
* ''increment_var'' for counters
* ''set_flag'' for boolean progress markers

Use requirement expressions to gate choices and nodes, for example:
* ''flag:quest_started''
* ''var:reputation>=10''

== Triggers ==
Triggers allow event-driven node progression. Common categories:
* Player actions (item use/pickup, block interact, crafting)
* World state (dimension, weather, time/day)
* Combat (kill entity, boss kill)
* Discovery (biome/structure/region enter)
* Advanced checks (proximity, altitude/depth, health thresholds)

== Actions ==
Common actions include:
* Give items
* Teleport
* Run commands
* Send messages
* Play scene effects
* Spawn custom bosses

== Tips ==
* Keep node IDs stable and descriptive.
* Prefer event-driven triggers over high-frequency polling patterns.
* Start linear, then add conditional and weighted branches.

